  <description type="morphology">Trees  to 40m; trunk to 1m diam.; crown narrowly conic.  Bark  gray-brown to reddish brown.  Branches  horizontally spreading; twigs not pendent, rather stout, yellow-brown, densely pubescent to glabrate.  Buds  reddish brown, 5--8mm, apex acute.  Leaves  0.8--2.5(--3)cm, 4-angled in cross section, somewhat flexuous, yellow-green to dark green, not glaucous, bearing stomates on all surfaces, apex mostly acute to sharp-pointed.  Seed cones  2.3--4.5(--5)cm; scales broadly fan-shaped, broadest near apex, 8--12 × 8--12mm, stiff, margin at apex entire to irregularly toothed. 2 n =24.</description>
